  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "Ms. Ho still kept a small, worn photograph of that same group in her wallet, she admitted, a little embarrassed.",
      "zh": "何老師有點不好意思地承認，她皮夾裡到現在還留著同一張已經磨損的舊照片。"
    },
    {
      "en": "They didn't go back to Mr. Pan right away. Instead, they went to find Ms. Ho.",
      "zh": "他們沒有馬上回去找潘老師，而是先去找何老師。"
    },
    {
      "en": "She was surprised to see them again. \"Case one is already finished,\" she said, smiling.",
      "zh": "她很驚訝又看到他們：「案件一已經結束了，」她笑著說。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"It is,\" Coco said. \"But we found something with your club's name in it. The Ten Minute Club.\"",
      "zh": "Coco 說：「是的，但我們找到一個東西，上面有你們社團的名字，十分鐘社。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Ms. Ho's smile changed, just a little.",
      "zh": "何老師的笑容微微變了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"That name,\" she said, \"was used by more than one club, over the years.\"",
      "zh": "她說：「這個名字，這些年來不只一個社團用過。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Was one of your students named Pan?\" Bernice asked. \"A long time ago?\"",
      "zh": "Bernice 問：「你以前的學生裡，有沒有一個姓潘的？很久以前？」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Ms. Ho was quiet for a long moment, the same way she had been quiet in Chapter 3.",
      "zh": "何老師沉默了好一會兒，就像她在第三章那時一樣安靜。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"He was a quiet boy,\" she said finally. \"New to the school. He didn't talk much in class.\"",
      "zh": "她最後說：「他是個安靜的男孩，剛轉來學校，上課不太說話。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"He came to Sunrise Club every morning, without fail, for almost two years.\"",
      "zh": "「他每天早上都會來晨光社，從不缺席，持續了快兩年。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Those ten minutes were the only part of his day,\" she said, \"where nobody expected anything from him.\"",
      "zh": "她說：「那十分鐘，是他一天裡唯一沒有人對他有所期待的時刻。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Coco felt something change quietly inside her.",
      "zh": "Coco 覺得心裡有什麼東西悄悄地變了。"
    },
    {
      "en": "When the club ended, she said, that same quiet boy asked her one question: \"What happens to people like me, once the ten minutes are gone?\"",
      "zh": "社團結束的時候，她說，那個安靜的男孩問了她一個問題：「像我這樣的人，十分鐘沒了以後怎麼辦？」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"I didn't have a good answer then,\" Ms. Ho said. \"I still don't know if I do now.\"",
      "zh": "何老師說：「我那時候沒有一個好答案，現在也還是不確定有沒有。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice looked at Coco. Neither of them needed to say Mr. Pan's name out loud.",
      "zh": "Bernice 看著 Coco，他們兩個都不需要把潘老師的名字說出口。"
    },
    {
      "en": "That afternoon, they found Mr. Pan alone in the classroom, grading papers after everyone else had left.",
      "zh": "那天下午，他們在教室裡找到獨自一人的潘老師，其他人都走了，他還在改作業。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"We talked to Ms. Ho,\" Coco said quietly. \"We know about the Ten Minute Club.\"",
      "zh": "Coco 小聲說：「我們跟何老師談過了，我們知道十分鐘社的事。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mr. Pan put down his pen and didn't look surprised at all.",
      "zh": "潘老師放下筆，看起來一點也不驚訝。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"I wondered how long it would take,\" he said. \"You two ask better questions than I ever did.\"",
      "zh": "他說：「我在想你們什麼時候會查到，你們兩個問問題的能力比我當年強多了。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"So it's true,\" Bernice said. \"You started the podcast because of that club.\"",
      "zh": "Bernice 說：「所以是真的，你開始這個 podcast 是因為那個社團。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"I started it,\" Mr. Pan said, \"because nobody wrote down what those ten minutes meant to me. I wanted this school to notice things before they disappear, not fourteen years after.\"",
      "zh": "潘老師說：「我開始這個節目，是因為沒有人寫下那十分鐘對我的意義。我希望這間學校能在事情消失之前就注意到，而不是十四年後才發現。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "As a teenager, Mr. Pan had been quiet, a little lonely, and easily embarrassed in front of a large group.",
      "zh": "潘老師少年時期很安靜，有點孤單，在一大群人面前很容易不好意思。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Ms. Ho remembered him as polite, careful, and always the last student to leave the classroom.",
      "zh": "何老師記得他很有禮貌、做事謹慎，總是最後一個離開教室的學生。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mr. Pan admitted his own after-school routine was simple: a hot bath, a quiet dinner, and an early bedtime.",
      "zh": "潘老師坦承他放學後的日常很簡單：洗個熱水澡、安靜地吃晚餐，然後早早睡覺。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"It's not exciting,\" he said, \"but it's honest, and it works for me.\"",
      "zh": "他說：「這不算精采，但很老實，對我來說很有用。」"
    }
  ],
